</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Evening hymn (Ken's Tallis canon). 8 bars. Mostly ②m (Am) and ① (G).
- Am7 = ②m throughout. D7 = ⑤7. F#° → G (①). All diatonic.
- LH: 4 notes open throughout. RH: 2-note thirds and sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Am recurs as a pivot — LH A2-E3-A3-C#4 frame gives stability.
- Bar 4 D7 LH adds C#3 inside the chord for richer seventh texture.
- Final A-D-G cadence bars 7-8 stepwise bass descent: A-D-G.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Quiet, reflective opening. Builds to bar 5 (c5 melodic peak). Final G cadence bar 8.
- The repeated Am-D-G motion gives a smooth, circular feel appropriate for evening prayer.
-->
